         <abstract>
            <p>Angell and Wingler's "A Note on Expensing Versus Depreciating Under the Accelerated Cost Recovery System" failed to mention that the expensing alternative has a $5,000 limit (rising to $10,000 in 1986). This comment amends their article for the limitation as well as the ITC-related change in the ACRS in the 1982 tax law. The full-basis recovery alternative is shown to be almost always inferior to the reduced basis recovery choice.</p>
         </abstract>
